tweet: It’s such a joke that now the sentiment is becoming that if you understand cryptocurrencies, you are going to hold some LEO. And in many cases, people that are praising LEO were saying that BNB was a total cash grab/scam just a couple of months ago.

This is not saying that LEO or BNB won't give investors a great return because they very well could. But always remember that high levels of risk are typically associated with high potential returns. And LEO/BNB are certainly a much higher level of risk than already risky BTC/ETH

Unlike BTC/ETH and others, LEO is still just a (centralized) exchange token with pretty high regulatory risk - similarly to BNB. It's not censorship resistant and holding LEO/BNB has nothing to do with "understanding cryptocurrencies".
